<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06051163 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06051163 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  WINE; LIST  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Here are Anthony Dias Blue's tasting notes from recent releases available inBay Area stores. Wines are rated on the 100-point scale. The list is updatedweekly.;    1988 ANITNORI CASTELLO DELLA SALA, CERVARO, Tuscany, Italy ($21).Spicy and lovely with great balance and finesse, rich and beautifullystructured. (91)  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Food  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  CRITIC'S CHOICE  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     1989 ROBERT PEPI WINERY CHARDONNAY, Puncheon Reserve, Napa Valley ($20).Soft, lush and buttery with big oak and fat flavors of tropical fruit. (88);   1989 ZD WINES CHARDONNAY, California ($18). Lively and rich with good acidityand a balanced, ripe fruit finish with lots of American oak. (87);    1989CAYMUS VINEYARDS SAUVIGNON BLANC, Napa Valley ($9). Smoky and rich withtoasty, spicy flavors. Long and complex. (86);    1988 SIGNORELLO VINEYARDSPINOT NOIR, Reserve, Napa Valley ($25). Rich and lush with cherry and brownsugar, spice and oak. (92);    1987 CONN CREEK WINERY MERLOT, Barrel Select,Collins Vineyard, Napa Valley ($22). Balanced and clean, elegant and rich withgreat structure and finish. (88);    1987 BUEHLER VINEYARDS CABERNETSAUVIGNON, Napa Valley ($12). Clean and balanced with smoky and rich fruit.(86);    1987 CAIN CELLARS CABERNET SAUVIGNON, Estate, Napa Valley ($25). Lushand rich with bright acidity and lush berry fruit and lovely buttery oak. Agorgeous wine. (93);    Non-Vintage VEUVE CLIQUOT BRUT, CHAMPAGNE, France($30) The famous yellow label bubbly is toasty and crisp with lovely, creamytexture and lively fruit. (91);    Values of the week;  1989 ESTANCIACHARDONNAY, Monterey ($8). Pineapple and tropical fruit, clean and balanced,smooth texture. (85);    Non-Vintage HAYWOOD WINERY SPAGHETTI RED, California($5.50). Peppery, spicy, forward and clean with lively berry fruit and goodbalance. (84)  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Mornin